Well… here’s a short clip of last nights hunt…

No excuses, I didn’t lose my cool, I just didn’t pick a spot and settle my pin… I had it sitting low and my stupid brain said “SHOOT!”… the arrow passed at the bottom of the brisket, the deer didn’t know what was happening and actually almost gave me another shot (another 5 seconds) 

Again, no excuses… I had a mental lapse, it’s embarrassing and I’m disappointed in myself. Period. 

Now I’m in the same stand looking to redeem myself with that buck or another. 

Wouldn’t bet against me on the next shot…

Image sequence of the recent #texas javelina kill. I’ve been running around the state (finally back home) and haven’t had time to post much! Well, get ready for a barrel of video and images lol. 

The javelina turned out to be a little more difficult than we anticipated, we drove non stop for two straight days and didn’t see any from the high rack truck. We finally got on a group coming into some well placed food (bird seed haha) and I was able to make the opportunity count! @garrett_chasinthedreamtv laid down the footage!

#bowhunting #javelina #texasbiggameslam #hunting #biggame #hoyttaggedout #hoytbowhunting #hhasport #cobraarchery #ozcutbroadheads 

Btw, I shot it 3 times cause it let me keep shooting it… and I didn’t want it to get away…

To cap off the #texasbiggameslam extravaganza is an elk… a freakin ELK in texas. Haha. Crazy humbled to have the opportunity to chase one in SW Texas after an invite from @hawks_h 

We seen upwards of 15-20 bulls the first morning out (a couple of real hammers too) but I wasn’t going to pass on a shot on a decent elk! Haha. While moving some ground in the truck, to reposition our perch, we came across this bad boy at point blank range in a dried creek bed. I jumped out of the truck and let her rip! After my bull went down, a bigger bull ran out of cover and Hawks was able to get a shot (or three) off and downed his bull! 

Was an incredible ending to an incredible experience in Texas during the 2022 season! I can absolutely not wait to begin putting this content together and sharing the whole story soon!

Right now I need some rest! Haha. 

#hunting #biggame #elk #elkhunting #texas #texashunting #myworldoutdoors

My team lost, so football is stupid for a few more months…. But this is a game day must have… 

It’s SOOO good!

Ingredients
1 - 8 oz. pack of cream cheese
1/4 cup diced jalepenos
1/2 cup cheddar cheese
1/2 cup pepperjack cheese
6 strips of bacon (diced)
Tablespoon minced garlic
2 beaten eggs
1 cup Italian flavored bread crumbs
1/4 cup diced sausage

Directions
- In large bowl. Mix together cheese, jalepenos, sausage, bacon, garlic
- Place ~1 1/2” balls onto parchment lined baking sheet
- Freeze for at least 30 minutes (until they freeze through)
- Remove from freezer, wash in egg, cover in bread crumbs
- Place in deep fryer at 350 degrees until crust is golden brown

Finally got around to fixing the pool decking, the stain was chipping and peeling already, but some recent hail storms put it into a whole new category… so we fixed that!

Super happy with how she turned out, seems very durable and the lighter color will help with the scorching concrete in the OK heat! I’ve used @rustoleum 2 part epoxy paints before and they are wicked tough. This is a first time using the @stonecoatcountertop paint flakes came in 55 pound bags (we used about 100 pounds for this 900 Ft decking) but they look amazing against the grey base layer. 

One thing I didn’t have any video or images of was the coping, that’s tintable epoxy paint from Rustoleum

Growing up, dove season was always the kick-off to hunting season, we would always have a big group of people at my Grandpa’s and we would always have the greatest time with the camaraderie of being back afield after a long rest. 

Well I started traveling and hunting back in 2006 and I don’t think I’ve dove hunted since, the family group hunt fell apart not long after that (apparently I was the glue that held it together lol). Flash forward to 2023 and some buddies and I have a new property in the Oklahoma panhandle (51 Ranch) that is covered up in birdies… so I decided to get the band back together and host it after the long hiatus!

I was so proud of my girls for coming up and experiencing their first dove hunt, they loved it! I loved it! Momma loved it! I think the rest of the folks loved it! Haha. 

And to have the rest of my family there (not everyone, but dad, grandpa, uncle Winford and my mom) , the ones that helped push me into the outdoors so many years ago. I was proud to see them have such a great time, not just afield but also all the in between moments.

Miss big hunts like that!! Looking forward to many more in the future!

Well… I did everything right last night except execute the draw back and shot…. 

I have no idea why this deer reacted so rashly…. He was looking the other way and calm… I drew back…. he heard just a little bit…. swung his head around…. and immediately sprinted away…. 

He ran to a couple hundred yards and began feeding in the wheat like nothing happened…. The does that were in front of me just put their heads back down and went to eating….

Oh well…. I’ll be back out there soon to try her again!

Man, this year as has been a rough one for ol’ Brandon “BA” “Flat Bill” “You’re Favorite Guy With A Bow” Adams … and a couple days ago kinda encapsulated my whole year, pretty cool… but not falling my way!

This big ol buck showed up on the @reconeco_outdoors over a @tectonic_usa feeder in daylight, I knew he would be bedded close because he was on the camera at 10 and 11.30 am….

Well… I walked in several hours before sunset and found out that he’s bedded exactly 21.1 yards away from the feeder…. Directly underneath the deer stand…. And he jumped up upon hearing me approach….Whoopsie.

I knelt down and filmed him (all within 70 yards) for about 30 minutes… he never really pegged me, but he knew I was something he didn’t want to be around (that’s a fact) and eventually blew and spooked…. FUN! 

It was cool to be that close to him, wish I could’ve gotten a shot… there’s still lots of season left and Sand Plum Canyon in western OK is CRAWLING with bucks I’ll send one towards! So don’t count me out.

Well, my hunting season may have came to a close… and it didn’t come out exactly the way I planned it. 

Pretty humbling year to say the least. I didn’t have any major mistakes or misses… just death by a thousand cuts to my ego with a seemingly endless supply of wrong decisions. 

Should’ve been “there” instead of “here”, then “here” when I moved to “there” or having mature bucks (2 to be exact) at 20 yards and be seconds away from certain death… only to escape unharmed… 

I’ll regroup and prepare to be better next season… I’ll continue to make the best decisions I can, with the information I have at hand. If I can, good things will happen in the long run (as admittedly they’ve been happening to me in the last 10 or so seasons).

But I’m ready to be better and capitalize when another opportunity arises!

#bowhunting #hunting #deer #deerhunting #whitetail #muledeer
